  "schema:name": "PHASE Crop Phenological Development Dataset (1993–2024) Version 1.1.2",
  "schema:version": "1.1.2",
  "schema:dateModified": "2026-03-16T00:00:00Z",
  "schema:description": "Germany-wide 1 km resolution continuous time series of interpolated day-of-year (DOY) values for crop phenological phases (plants 202, 203, 204, 205, 207, 208, 215). The dataset was generated using a generalized additive model (GAM) applied to phenological observations from DWD and JKI. Each phase-year combination provides three components: (1) DOY prediction raster, (2) local uncertainty layer derived as Bayesian Additive Model (BAM) posterior standard error (BSE), and (3) validation accuracy metrics (VAM) in CSV format. Temporal coverage spans mostly 1993–2024, with documented exceptions for specific crops and phases (e.g. missing data for crop 207 before 2014 and crop 208 in 2023–2024, as well as isolated phase-year gaps such as 203-15_2022 and 205-17_2022).",

  "schema:url": "https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.<RECORD_ID>",



  "schema:relatedLink": [
    "https://doi.org/10.20387/bonares-je6g-9896"
  ],


